text.tspan: Female labor force participation rates by national per capita income, 2020
The labor force participation rate corresponds to the proportion of the population ages 15 and older that is
economically active. National income levels correspond to GDP per capita in constant international dollars. This
means figures are adjusted for inflation and cross-country price differences.
Source: Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
